The paper discusses the implementation of a hybrid approach for the coexistence of traditional IP routing with SDN based forwarding within the same provider domain. This makes it likely that the paper belongs to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the design and implementation of advanced services like Pseudo Wires and Virtual Switches, which are related to System and Control (cs.SY) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the design and implementation of management tools for the emulation of the proposed solution, which is related to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance evaluation of the deployed solution, which is related to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
